TopicTitle: [1.1.3] Procedural Parts - Parts the way you want 'em - v1.2.5 July 3

Articles.Content:
49 minutes ago, mecki said:

I'm on 1.2.2 and I don't have any controls to change the size of my parts when I right-click.

Is this to due to my up-to-date KSP version?

I don't have any issues in 1.2.2 with 51 mods running

11 minutes ago, Rafael acevedo said:

I don't have any issues in 1.2.2 with 51 mods running

Thanks for the feedback!

I checked again.

I hadn't played KSP for a long time. CKAN didn't update Procedural Parts since it isn't compatible with my current KSP version.

I updated manually and now it works.

4 hours ago, mecki said:

I'm on 1.2.2 and I don't have any controls to change the size of my parts when I right-click.

Is this to due to my up-to-date KSP version?

Module Manager? And do you have the mo installed correctly? Like GameDate/procedural parts/..

Or is it: GameData/GameData/procedural parts/..

I have an extremely low fps using this mod, stock 55 fps with the mod (used) 3 fps.

Does anyone else have this problem or is it just my pc (KSP version 1.2.2)

Also does anyone have a fix for it ?

 

Thanks in advance.

Edited February 6, 2017 by niskan
Not enough info given.

I don't have any issues and I am cunning over 51 other mods. What version of ksp you are using 64 or 32 bits, also true this due a stock install add parts first see impact to fps, continue to add mos one by one until fps impacted

I don't know if it's this mod or Procedural Fairings. But in campaign mode if I pass a certain size and save then go to edit the parts, the parts Go all weird and Don't adjust anymore. Also on the launch pad Fairings fall on their own and Fairing bases explode.
Whenever I use a procedural part, like a structural piece or a fuel tank, when I try to revert the game crashes, for all textures. How is this happening?

Am I the only one with issues? To where in campaign mode if I make my procedural parts past a certain size things get wonky? They loose the mount points and shape and become uneditable? Or is it that there is a limit to the amount of parts that are procedural? I was able to build up my 2 top stages no problems but then when I get to my lower stage and save.. then reload All the bugs start to happen.

 

as soon as you save and reload this happens... I've tried many things Size.. part number Fairing bases it seems to do this all the time.

 

 

 

Edited February 15, 2017 by Dermeister

Is nobody else having a problem where installing Procedural Parts causes the entire parts list to be completely empty? Does anybody even know what sort of problem or conflict could cause a bug like that?

2 hours ago, baldamundo said:

Is nobody else having a problem where installing Procedural Parts causes the entire parts list to be completely empty? Does anybody even know what sort of problem or conflict could cause a bug like that?

I haven't seen this in P.P. Before. What other mods are you running? I doubt it's a conflict. I run about 100+ mods including Procedural Parts. Can you tell us what game version, is Module Manager installed.... install process.... Etc...

Looks like you've been here a while so I think you know what I'm asking.

I have problem. All of stock textures from PP are disapered. But textures from custom packs works. I`ve reinstalled it a lot times.

edit: OH, iremoved SETI`s textures for PP and now it works. That may be a bug.

Edited February 19, 2017 by Nick233

running into a couple issues, firstly when installing and then running, i get a message that says procedural parts is not compatible, i'm running ksp 1.2.2, and i have the 1.2.8 version of PP. Second which may not be related to PP but hoping to find a captain, is, well, let me preface this with i know how to eva. That said, i'm on a rescue mission, planes are matched, velocities are matched, have save in place, i switch to target vessel, send stranded kerbal to eva, and lose control of everything other then looking around, he's still held on to the vessel, and i can see the messages to B: board and Spacebar: let go. Neither button works, i can't climb in any direction, i can't quicksave or reload, but it's not frozen as the universe is still turning and i can look around. So um... help?

Hello, everyone. I was wondering, is there an easy way to convert the procedural life support tank to USI Supplies?

Thanks in advance!

How do this parts compare to KW/Stock as far as cost/unit of fuel is concerned?(In a previous version i had tried they were quite expensive)

I am thinking of deleting all fuel tanks from my save,

would you say i could replace them efficiently with this mod?
